<title>USA: Central Power freed to lift debt limits.</title>
<headline>Central Power freed to lift debt limits.</headline>
<dateline>DALLAS 1997-04-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Central Power and Light Co on Tuesday said its shareholders had adopted an amendment to eliminate a provision restricting the amount of unsecured debt it is able to issue.</p>
<p>The adoption was the result of its proxy solicitation of preferred and common shareholders at a special meeting Monday.</p>
<p>The company said all its outstanding common shares, which are owned by its parent, Central and South West Corp, were voted in favor of the amendment.</p>
